title: Misaki Doi claims maiden WTA title with victory in Luxembourg
text:
Misaki Doi claims maiden WTA title with victory in Luxembourg 25 Oct 2015 18:32:01 
comments 
Misaki Doi claimed her first WTA Tour title with a three-set win over Mona Barthel at the Luxembourg Open. 
The Japanese player, who is ranked 92nd in the world, overcame her experienced German opponent 6-4 6-7 (7/9) 6-0 in the final. 
Doi beat former world number one Jelena Jankovic in the quarter-finals and reached her maiden final after her semi-final opponent Alison Van Uytvanck retired when trailing 6-4, citing a viral illness. 
The 24-year-old Yokohama-born Doi can claim a place alongside Caroline Wozniacki, Venus Williams and Victoria Azarenka as winners of the Luxembourg title. Related Sport News
